description: Two beach houses in Rodanthe, North Carolina, have been purchased by the National Park Service in an effort to avoid the uncontrollable collapse of the eroded structures. The houses costed $700,000.

title: Western Sydney residents slam Waleed Aly and ABC hosts who said No voters were 'too dumb' to understand the Voice to Parliament
description: Waleed Aly and Patricia Karvelas have been slammed over comments they made about how the education, income and geographic location of Aussies affected the outcome of the Voice.

title: President Biden heading to Israel Wednesday as conflict with Hamas rages on with both sides sending rockets into neighborhoods
description: Joe Biden will arrive in Israel on Wednesday, Antony Blinken confirmed on Monday night.

title: Rapper Lady Leshurr, 35, 'attacked her ex-girlfriend and bit her new partner's ear in late-night bust up', court hears
description: The 35-year-old artist, real name Melesha O'Garro, is accused of attacking her ex-girlfriend Sidnee Hussein and Chante Boyea in an altercation in Walthamstow, east London on October 22, 2022.

title: Seven out of 10 adults in the UK are targeted by scams in the past year as 13% lose their cash to fraud, study finds
description: A study of 2,000 adults found that 7 per cent of people had lost as much as £5,000. It emerged the scams most prevalent this year were phishing (37 per cent).

title: Veteran Tory MP Peter Bone faces suspension for alleged bullying and sexual misconduct in sleaze scandal that could trigger yet ANOTHER by-election
description: Peter Bone was found by a parliamentary watchdog to have 'committed many varied acts of bullying and one act of sexual misconduct' against a young man who worked in his Westminster office.

title: Victoria high school students take muck-up day too far with teachers egged and police called
description: Year 12 students across Victoria have been accused of taking their Muck Up activities too far with police forced to attend one school after thousands of dollars worth of damage was caused.

title: Pupils in England could soon take GCSE and A-level exams on computers under new plans for teenagers to study at least one major subject digitally by 2030
description: An AQA report said the first digital exams will largely replicate the paper exams on screen but there is potential for 'more innovative and interactive assessment' in the longer term.

title: Adelaide fruit shop owner divides Aussies for sharing video of controversial Voice act
description: A famously foul-mouthed fruit shop owner has come under fire for posting a video of a car making a detour to run over a Voice Yes23 campaign sign in the middle of a roundabout..
